   <section class="elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-395cc41 elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default" data-element_type="section" data-id="395cc41">
    <div class="elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default">
     <div class="elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-fcd2278" data-element_type="column" data-id="fcd2278">
      <div class="elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated">
       <div class="elementor-element elementor-element-b8a2bde elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading" data-element_type="widget" data-id="b8a2bde" data-widget_type="heading.default">
        <div class="elementor-widget-container">
         <h2 class="elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default">
          crinacle's
         </h2>
        </div>
       </div>
       <div class="elementor-element elementor-element-f300866 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading" data-element_type="widget" data-id="f300866" data-widget_type="heading.default">
        <div class="elementor-widget-container">
         <h1 class="elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default">
          ranking list
         </h1>
        </div>
       </div>
       <div class="elementor-element elementor-element-bc4978c elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading" data-element_type="widget" data-id="bc4978c" data-widget_type="heading.default">
        <div class="elementor-widget-container">
         <h2 class="elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default">
          Headphones
         </h2>
        </div>
       </div>
      </div>
     </div>
    </div>
   </section>
   <section class="elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-1b07b18 elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default" data-element_type="section" data-id="1b07b18">
    <div class="elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default">
     <div class="elementor-column elementor-col-50 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-5490ef0" data-element_type="column" data-id="5490ef0">
      <div class="elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated">
       <div class="elementor-element elementor-element-426b838 elementor-widget__width-initial elementor-widget-tablet__width-initial elementor-widget-mobile__width-initial elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor" data-element_type="widget" data-id="426b838" data-widget_type="text-editor.default">
        <div class="elementor-widget-container">
         <style>
          .elementor-widget-text-editor.elementor-drop-cap-view-stacked .elementor-drop-cap{background-color:#69727d;color:#fff}.elementor-widget-text-editor.elementor-drop-cap-view-framed .elementor-drop-cap{color:#69727d;border:3px solid;background-color:transparent}.elementor-widget-text-editor:not(.elementor-drop-cap-view-default) .elementor-drop-cap{margin-top:8px}.elementor-widget-text-editor:not(.elementor-drop-cap-view-default) .elementor-drop-cap-letter{width:1em;height:1em}.elementor-widget-text-editor .elementor-drop-cap{float:left;text-align:center;line-height:1;font-size:50px}.elementor-widget-text-editor .elementor-drop-cap-letter{display:inline-block}
         </style>
         <h2 style="text-align: center;">
          <span style="text-decoration: underline; font-size: 24pt;">
           <span style="color: #000000;">
            <strong>
             <span style="font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif;">
              GRADES
             </span>
            </strong>
           </span>
          </span>
         </h2>
         <p>
          <span style="font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt; color: #000000;">
           <strong>
            S
           </strong>
           : Must try. Experience what the best has to offer.
          </span>
          <br/>
          <span style="font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt; color: #000000;">
           <strong>
            A
           </strong>
           : While not at the top of the summit, Grade-A headphones are still very respectable performers that would still be considered as some of the best by many.
          </span>
          <br/>
          <span style="font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt; color: #000000;">
           <strong>
            B
           </strong>
           : Can essentially be described as “very good”, or excellent performers in their own right.
          </span>
          <br/>
          <span style="font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt; color: #000000;">
           <strong>
            C
           </strong>
           : Average in the grand scheme of things, anywhere from “passable” to “good”.
          </span>
          <br/>
          <span style="font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt; color: #000000;">
           <strong>
            D
           </strong>
           : The threshold for “bad” starts here.
          </span>
          <br/>
          <span style="font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt; color: #000000;">
           <strong>
            E
           </strong>
           : The truly horrible.
          </span>
          <br/>
          <span style="font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt; color: #000000;">
           <strong>
            F
           </strong>
           : The failures. One needs to literally sound broken to reach the depths of F-tier.
          </span>
         </p>
        </div>
       </div>
       <div class="elementor-element elementor-element-81e1de2 elementor-widget__width-initial elementor-widget-tablet__width-initial elementor-widget-mobile__width-initial elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor" data-element_type="widget" data-id="81e1de2" data-widget_type="text-editor.default">
        <div class="elementor-widget-container">
         <h2 style="text-align: center;">
          <span style="text-decoration: underline; font-size: 24pt;">
           <span style="color: #000000;">
            <strong>
             <span style="font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif;">
              Value Rating
             </span>
            </strong>
           </span>
          </span>
         </h2>
         <p>
          <span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif;">
           ★: “Worth the price” (MSRP)
          </span>
          <br/>
          <span style="font-size: 8pt; font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif;">
           – Only those with a grade of “C” or above are considered for their first star.
           <br/>
          </span>
          <span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif;">
           <span style="font-size: 8pt;">
            – Discontinued models are not eligible.
           </span>
           <br/>
          </span>
          <span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif;">
           ★★: “Redefines the price bracket”
           <br/>
          </span>
          <span style="font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;">
           ★★★: “Worth the Blind”
           <br/>
          </span>
          <span style="font-size: 8pt; font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif;">
           – Needs to be eligible for at least a ★ rating before ★★★ can be considered.
          </span>
          <br/>
          <span style="font-size: 8pt; font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif;">
           – Discontinued models may still be considered.
          </span>
         </p>
        </div>
       </div>
       <div class="elementor-element elementor-element-da21796 elementor-widget__width-initial elementor-widget-tablet__width-initial elementor-widget-mobile__width-initial elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor" data-element_type="widget" data-id="da21796" data-widget_type="text-editor.default">
        <div class="elementor-widget-container">
         <p style="text-align: center;">
          <em>
           <span style="font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt; color: #000000;">
            “You’re the measurements guy! You measure more than you listen! I’m not going to listen to you!
           </span>
          </em>
          <em>
           <span style="font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt; color: #000000;">
            “
           </span>
          </em>
         </p>
         <p style="text-align: left;">
          <span style="font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt; color: #000000;">
           Great, I’m not telling you to. My work on measurements is separate from my reviewing work. It takes me 5 minutes to measure a headphone, you honestly think I don’t have time to listen to it as well?
          </span>
         </p>
         <h2 style="text-align: center;">
          <span style="color: #000000; font-size: 18pt;">
           <strong>
            <span style="text-decoration: underline;">
             <span style="font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif;">
              ↓↓↓ READ THIS: Notes &amp; Disclaimers ↓↓↓
             </span>
            </span>
           </strong>
          </span>
         </h2>
         <ul>
          <li>
           <span style="font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt; color: #000000;">
            <strong>
             The headphones are ranked purely by sonic performance.
            </strong>
            Fit, isolation, durability, build quality etc. are ignored unless they interfere with the sound itself.
           </span>
           <ul>
            <li>
             <span style="font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt; color: #000000;">
              <strong>
               The headphones are not ranked in terms of price-to-performance value.
              </strong>
              They are ranked according to what I think is “objectively” the best.
             </span>
            </li>
           </ul>
          </li>
          <li>
           <span style="font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt; color: #000000;">
            Most of the headphones in this list are determined based off demo units from shops.
           </span>
           <ul>
            <li>
             <span style="font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt; color: #000000;">
              Rankings will only consider
              <strong>
               stock pads
              </strong>
              (or pads provided out of the box). Third party pads (apart from “stock replacement” pads designed for a specific headphone) are
              <strong>
               not
              </strong>
              a consideration in this ranking list.
             </span>
            </li>
           </ul>
          </li>
          <li>
           <span style="font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt; color: #000000;">
            <strong>
             The positions are not set in stone.
            </strong>
            I’m only human; I may miss out on certain details or traits that may only be apparent with repeated listening. Expect changes.
           </span>
          </li>
          <li>
           <span style="font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt; color: #000000;">
            Ranks will be determined based on the best unit tried. Because of this, I am not accounting for unit variation. I cannot guarantee that what I’m hearing is what you will be hearing.
           </span>
           <ul>
            <li>
             <span style="font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt; color: #000000;">
              This will revert to the most recent unit tried if there is a significant time gap between the last and most recent times I tried a particular model.
             </span>
            </li>
           </ul>
          </li>
          <li>
           <span style="font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt; color: #000000;">
            Prices are at MSRP in USD. Prices not directly available in USD are based off the exchange rate during the time of writing.
           </span>
           <ul>
            <li>
             <span style="font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;">
              The price of any additional compulsory component (e.g. electrostatic energisers) will be added to this MSRP value and valued accordingly.
             </span>
            </li>
            <li>
             <span style="font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;">
              With enough requests, a headphone may also be tested with a different (typically more expensive) amplifier. If the community deems this amplifier as “necessary” for said headphone, the price of the amplifier will also be added to the MSRP value and valued accordingly.
             </span>
            </li>
           </ul>
          </li>
          <li>
           <span style="font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;">
            All headphones are tested on the iFi iDSD micro Black Label, unless otherwise indicated.
           </span>
           <ul>
            <li>
             <span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif;">
              Headphones are occasionally tested on the Motu M2 and Topping A90, but final ranks are determined according to performance on the micro Black Label unless performance is deemed superior on the A90, in which case it will also be indicated as such.
             </span>
            </li>
           </ul>
          </li>
          <li>
           <span style="font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt; color: #000000;">
            A (non-complete) list of headphones that I’ve tried can be found on
            <a data-ytta-id="-" href="http://crinacle.com/graph-database/" style="color: #000000;">
             <span style="font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;">
              my measure
             </span>
             ments database
            </a>
            .
           </span>
           <ul>
            <li>
             <span style="font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt; color: #000000;">
              If you can tell, some headphones on the database (that I’ve tried) are not in this list. This is could be due to lack of interest or lack of enough ear time to make a proper decision on tier placement.
             </span>
            </li>
           </ul>
          </li>
          <li>
           <span style="font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt; color: #000000;">
            <strong>
             Yes, this is the opinion of one person on the internet.
            </strong>
            Please do not get too offended if your favourite headphone isn’t graded as highly as you’d like. (vice versa applies)
           </span>
          </li>
          <li>
           <span style="font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt; color: #000000;">
            <strong>
             This list is meant to be used as a reference point.
            </strong>
            I highly recommend against blind-buying and suggest to have a listen to the headphones yourself. By all means, use this to shortlist what you should try in the future but don’t take it as gospel.
           </span>
          </li>
         </ul>
         <p>
          <span style="font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif; color: #000000;">
           To aid searching, ranks without the + or – symbol will be marked with a “=”. That also includes the E &amp; F ranks.
          </span>
         </p>
        </div>
       </div>
       <div class="elementor-element elementor-element-018c3c4 elementor-widget__width-initial elementor-widget-tablet__width-initial elementor-widget-mobile__width-initial elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor" data-element_type="widget" data-id="018c3c4" data-widget_type="text-editor.default">
        <div class="elementor-widget-container">
         <p style="text-align: center;">
          <span style="font-size: 12pt;">
           <span style="color: #000000; font-family: verdana, geneva, sans-serif;">
            <i>
             Remember:
            </i>
            <strong>
             You’re not supposed to agree 100% with this list, and that’s the point.
             <br/>
            </strong>
           </span>
          </span>
         </p>
        </div>
       </div>

            <div class="elementor-container elementor-column-gap-narrow">
             <div class="elementor-column elementor-col-50 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-a6e43e7" data-element_type="column" data-id="a6e43e7">
              <div class="elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated">
               <div class="elementor-element elementor-element-131efe2 elementor-hidden-desktop elementor-hidden-tablet elementor-widget elementor-widget-image" data-element_type="widget" data-id="131efe2" data-widget_type="image.default">

               <div class="elementor-element elementor-element-e82eb87 elementor-hidden-desktop elementor-hidden-tablet elementor-widget elementor-widget-image" data-element_type="widget" data-id="e82eb87" data-widget_type="image.default">
                <div class="elementor-widget-container">
                 <a href="https://crinacle.com/midnight">
                  <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-image-19866" decoding="async" height="250" loading="lazy" src="https://crinacle.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/HiFiGo-IEF.jpg" width="300"/>
                 </a>
                </div>
               </div>
               <div class="elementor-element elementor-element-14fa35e elementor-hidden-desktop elementor-hidden-tablet elementor-widget elementor-widget-image" data-element_type="widget" data-id="14fa35e" data-widget_type="image.default">
                <div class="elementor-widget-container">
                 <a href="https://shenzhenaudio.com/products/moondrop-x-crinacle-blessing2-dusk-1dd-4ba-in-ear-monitor-earphone">
                  <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-image-11594" decoding="async" height="250" loading="lazy" src="https://crinacle.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/SZA_Ad_Dusk.jpg" width="300"/>
                 </a>
                </div>
